decision_conditions:
CONDITION:  Before the development hereby permitted is commenced full particulars, detailed drawings (including sections, elevational and threshold treatments) to a large scale (1:20) and samples in respect of the following items shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the particulars so approved:

a.	Removal, restoration and reinstallation of the brick paviours and all other historic finishes in their current locations;
b.	works to internal and external features, including doors; gutters, down pipes, windows; floor surfacing, floor/supporting beams; and signage;
c.	design details (including junctions particulars) of all demolition, infill and extension works to the listed building, which includes the residential accommodation;
d.	repainting and where relevant cleaning of brickwork;
e.	details of the extraction, ventilation and filtration equipment and any other external plant or machinery (including ventilation units and air intake louvres)

REASON:  To maintain and enhance the character and appearance of the Grade II Listed Building and Kings Cross Conservation Area as empowered by Section 74(3) of the Town and Country Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990.
